"{\"uid\": \"themoscowtimes.com-2024-07-28-russia-says-journalists-stripped-of-olympic-accreditation-a85856\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Russia's TASS state news agency said Sunday the Paris Olympics organizing committee had stripped four of its journalists of accreditation to cover the Games after they attended initial events.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999981683466507, \"rank\": 1.4582519987317226e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 9, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.418066859589922e-36, \"text\": \"TASS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TASS said that the removal of the reporters' accreditation, essential to cover the Games, was \\\"completely unexpected\\\" after the journalists had entered France, received passes and attended the opening and several events.\", \"from\": 194, \"to\": 414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 194, \"end\": 198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.418066859589922e-36, \"text\": \"TASS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\"}, {\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.753526565555699, \"rank\": 0.28936072576695765, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Paris 2024 Organizing Committee... cited the decision of the authorities of France, but did not mention any concrete grievances and reasons for such a decision,\\\" the agency said in a statement.\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 497, \"end\": 503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.753526565555699, \"rank\": 0.28936072576695765, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the journalists, Artyom Kuznetsov, was covering his seventh Olympics, TASS said.\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 640, \"end\": 656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artyom_Kuznetsov\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Artyom Kuznetsov\", \"types\": [\"Q847400\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artyom_Kuznetsov\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artyom_Kuznetsov\"}, {\"begin\": 693, \"end\": 697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.418066859589922e-36, \"text\": \"TASS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Contacted by AFP, the International Olympic Committee and the French Foreign Ministry did not immediately respond to requests for comment.\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 718, \"end\": 721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1256689345948224e-16, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}, {\"begin\": 727, \"end\": 758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_for_Europe_and_Foreign_Affairs\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Foreign Ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_for_Europe_and_Foreign_Affairs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_for_Europe_and_Foreign_Affairs\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier, some Russian journalists had accreditation requests denied, prompting Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Maria Zakharova to tell TASS that \\\"observing the rights of journalists and providing freedom of speech are just empty sounds for [President Emmanuel] Macron and his gang.\\\"\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 924, \"end\": 940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Foreign_Office\", \"score\": 0.8214354370848955, \"rank\": 0.21616475797578075, \"text\": \"Foreign Ministry\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Foreign_Office\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_Foreign_Office\"}, {\"begin\": 953, \"end\": 968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maria Zakharova\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\"}, {\"begin\": 977, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.418066859589922e-36, \"text\": \"TASS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just 15 Russian athletes have been accredited to compete at the Olympics as neutrals as most sports have banned Russians and their allies in response to Moscow's military operation in Ukraine.\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1238, \"end\": 1246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russians\", \"score\": 0.9256996839851892, \"rank\": 0.08026284502373299, \"text\": \"Russians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russians\"}, {\"begin\": 1279, \"end\": 1285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 0.9999999999974989, \"rank\": 2.380011676126187e-12, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}, {\"begin\": 1310, \"end\": 1317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9945152366985532, \"rank\": 0.0055150107756903955, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few days before the opening of the Games, French police arrested a Russian man suspected of plotting acts of \\\"destabilization\\\" during the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1364, \"end\": 1377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.495358170577632e-37, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French prosecutors said the man, born in 1984, was suspected of \\\"passing intelligence to a foreign power in order to arouse hostilities in France,\\\" a charge punishable by up to 30 years in prison.\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1477, \"end\": 1483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9859462859366447, \"rank\": 0.00953959501190289, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1616, \"end\": 1622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.753526565555699, \"rank\": 0.28936072576695765, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Le Monde and other media named the suspect as Kirill Gryaznov, a chef originally from the city of Perm in the Urals.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1791, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1721, \"end\": 1727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriarch_Kirill_of_Moscow\", \"score\": 0.999999999891088, \"rank\": 1.0896361034523619e-10, \"text\": \"Kirill\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriarch_Kirill_of_Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriarch_Kirill_of_Moscow\"}, {\"begin\": 1773, \"end\": 1777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perm_Oblast\", \"score\": 0.9886754388736951, \"rank\": 0.011270521083858476, \"text\": \"Perm\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perm_Oblast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perm_Oblast\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Russia gave the opening ceremony a critical reception, with Zakharova describing it as a \\\"massive failure.\\\"\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1793, \"end\": 1799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999981683466507, \"rank\": 1.4582519987317226e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TASS wrote the opening \\\"was notable for a number of awkward situations,\\\" noting gaffes such as the Olympic flag raised upside-down and viewers leaving early due to pouring rain.\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 2079, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1902, \"end\": 1906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.418066859589922e-36, \"text\": \"TASS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TASS\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Message from The Moscow Times:  Dear readers,  We are facing unprecedented challenges.\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2096, \"end\": 2112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Moscow Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Russia's Prosecutor General's Office has designated The Moscow Times as an \\\"undesirable\\\" organization, criminalizing our work and putting our staff at risk of prosecution.\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2170, \"end\": 2176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999981683466507, \"rank\": 1.4582519987317226e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2179, \"end\": 2197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prosecutor-General_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999994086003355, \"rank\": 5.913768863516193e-07, \"text\": \"Prosecutor General\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prosecutor-General_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prosecutor-General_of_Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2222, \"end\": 2238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Moscow Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This follows our earlier unjust labeling as a \\\"foreign agent.\\\"\", \"from\": 2342, \"to\": 2404, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These actions are direct attempts to silence independent journalism in Russia.\", \"from\": 2406, \"to\": 2484, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2477, \"end\": 2483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999981683466507, \"rank\": 1.4582519987317226e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The authorities claim our work \\\"discredits the decisions of the Russian leadership.\\\"\", \"from\": 2485, \"to\": 2569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We see things differently: we strive to provide accurate, unbiased reporting on Russia.\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999981683466507, \"rank\": 1.4582519987317226e-06, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We, the journalists of The Moscow Times, refuse to be silenced.\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2682, \"end\": 2698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Moscow Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But to continue our work,we need your help.\", \"from\": 2723, \"to\": 2766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your support, no matter how small, makes a world of difference.\", \"from\": 2768, \"to\": 2831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you can, please support us monthly starting from just$2.It's quick to set up, and every contribution makes a significant impact.\", \"from\": 2832, \"to\": 2963, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By supporting The Moscow Times, you are defending open, independent journalism in the face of repression.\", \"from\": 2965, \"to\": 3070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2979, \"end\": 2995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Moscow Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Moscow_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you for standing with us.\", \"from\": 3071, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": []}]}"